Salsa fresca is our favorite way to channel warm-weather vibes all year round. It's juicy and tangy with a touch of heat, making it the perfect complement to crispy, turmeric-and-cumin-spiced barramundi. The fillets are served on top of steamy quinoa and blanketed in lime crema and said salsa. No matter the temperature, one bite of this delicious dish will make everything feel a whole lot sunnier.

== Salsa Fresca ==

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Halve @grape tomatoes{4}. Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(minced). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Mince @chili pepper{1}(minced).

> For 4 servings, zest one lime and quarter both.

== Quinoa ==

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the scallion whites and @turmeric{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings); cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

> You'll use more turmeric later.

Add @water{1%cup}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1%unit}, and @salt{big pinch}. Bring to a boil, then stir in @white quinoa{1/2%cup}. Cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until quinoa is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Crème ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp}, a big squeeze of lime juice from half the remaining lime, and as much lime zest as you like. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Spice Mixture ==

In a second small bowl, combine @cumin{1%tsp} and @turmeric{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings).

> Be sure to measure the turmeric—we sent more.

== Barramundi ==

Pat @barramundi{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with salt and pepper. Season flesh sides with spice mixture.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add barramundi skin sides down and cook until skin is crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Flip and cook until fish is opaque and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

== To Serve ==

Fluff quinoa with a fork; stir in scallion greens and @butter{1%tbsp} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide between plates. Top quinoa with barramundi; garnish with salsa fresca and crema. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.